<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1316,1773]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1567,1592]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species differs from other diadematoids found in 
<collectingCountry box="[986,1102,1567,1592]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
by having a very low test, conspicuously elongated, narrow genital plates, and spines in which the shaft is partially filled with a loose stereom meshwork.
</paragraph>
